That, at the sitting on Thursday 4th November, notwithstanding the provisions of Standing Order No. 14 (Exempted business), the Speaker shall put the Questions necessary to dispose of proceedings on:


(a) the Motions in the name of Mr Tony Newton relating to Members' Pensions not later than one and a half hours after the commencement of proceedings on the first such Motion;

(b) the Motions in the name of Mr Tony Newton relating to Parliamentary Questions and Notices of Questions not later than one and a half hours after the commencement of proceedings on the first such Motion; and

(c) the motion in the name of Mr Tony Newton relating to Financial Assistance to Opposition Parties not later than one and a half hours after their commencement;

including the Questions on any Amendments to the said Motions which she may have selected and which had not been moved by those respective hours; and the said Motions may be proceeded with after the expiry of the time for opposed business.—[Mr. Arbuthnot.]
